      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) reported for all quantities of interest; GCI below 5% for hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted. GCI for velocity fields was 3.2%, within tolerance. GCI for the hemolysis index itself was 14.7%, substantially exceeding the 5% threshold. Discretization error in the primary QoI is unacceptably high. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted under pulsatile flow conditions matching VAD operating envelope; fluid temperature, hematocrit, and shear history documented.",
      "rationale": "Available experimental data (FDA benchmark, Stewart et al. 2012) were collected under steady-state, constant-flow conditions. The COU requires pulsatile flow. Temperature and hematocrit were documented in the benchmark but shear history was not. The fundamental mismatch between steady-state test conditions and pulsatile COU conditions limits this factor to achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
