      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence criteria documented and demonstrated to be below 1e-6 for all residuals; time-step sensitivity study for pulsatile simulations.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was demonstrated to 1e-5 for steady-state runs. No time-step sensitivity study was performed because pulsatile simulations were not part of the validation activity. The absence of transient solver error characterisation is a significant gap for the pulsatile COU. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with peer-reviewed boundary condition specification; evidence that analyst training covers pulsatile hemolysis CFD.",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow is documented but has not been peer-reviewed. Analyst training records cover steady-state pump CFD; no evidence of specific training in pulsatile hemolysis simulation was provided. Use error controls are inadequate for MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model is appropriate for pulsatile flow; sensitivity analysis of model form assumptions.",
      "rationale": "Model form assessment was flagged as an epistemic gap. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model was selected without documented justification of its applicability to pulsatile flow regimes. Literature indicates the model was calibrated under steady shear conditions. No model form sensitivity study was performed. Marked not-assessed; achieved level recorded as 2 based on partial literature review only."
    },
