    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the simulation evidence package for regulatory submission on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ was performed and steady-state validation agreement was within 18%. The team noted that pulsatile validation data were unavailable but judged the steady-state FDA benchmark comparison sufficient as a surrogate, citing geometric similarity of the pump and the conservative nature of the hemolysis model. This rationale does not adequately address the fundamental regime mismatch between the steady-state comparator and the pulsatile COU, nor the absence of the comparedAgainst link in the primary validation result. Multiple credibility factors remain below required levels, and six factors were not assessed. The acceptance decision is not supported by the evidence as assembled.",
